{"TopicId":176026,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Retractable wings","CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-19T23:54:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-19T23:54:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t make it into orbit with a spaceplane mounted to a rocket, because it always flips over because of the wing, so retractable wings might help with that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AVaughan","CreatedById":152784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T03:23:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShuttle style lifters are easier than mounting a winged spaceplane\u00A0on top of a booster.\u00A0 \u00A0(That is never going to be aerodynamically stable).\u00A0 You can also do something similar to Falcon Heavy/Delta Heavy, and mount a pair on boosters on the spaceplane\u0027s wingtips and/or 2 pair of boosters attached to the wings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T10:07:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can balance it by adding fins to the back.\u00A0 Might be a lot of fins, but it\u0027ll get you... somewhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA few players have made retractable wings in stock I believe, but they might be too cumbersome for the average player / ship.\u00A0 Check the spacecraft exchange to see if you can find some.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoboRay","CreatedById":46556,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T13:05:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223402608\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529551388\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AVaughan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, AVaughan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0(That is never going to be aerodynamically stable).\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever say \u0022never\u0022...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Tb8KOK8.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Tb8KOK8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/9wlcx\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E[Mission Album]\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-21T13:06:50Z\u0022 title=\u002206/21/2018 01:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by RoboRay\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T18:42:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the past the only way I\u0027ve been able to get into orbit is to roll 90 degrees, so the ground is to your side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T21:16:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCarry it up in a drag neutral position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002237F9E605DF131ED9F8C4E295045D75916FB538F3\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/853856383481692087/37F9E605DF131ED9F8C4E295045D75916FB538F3/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen re-dock with it for a more re-entry friendly profile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002203892EE646287A686D11057701EE384E09A36F6A\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/853856383481861642/03892EE646287A686D11057701EE384E09A36F6A/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA bit unconventional, but it works!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227F01168815DD541737420F319983742328057EC0\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/853856383481861974/7F01168815DD541737420F319983742328057EC0/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-21T21:18:13Z\u0022 title=\u002206/21/2018 09:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T22:34:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting things with wings into orbit I don\u0027t think would be the main use. I think the real advantage is sticking things with wings in cargo bags and fairings. So.... I don\u0027t mind this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-21T23:48:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223402802\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529586337\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002246556\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoboRay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, RoboRay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever say \u0022never\u0022...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbsolutely gorgeous screenshot and rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy hats off to you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AVaughan","CreatedById":152784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-22T04:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223402802\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529586337\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002246556\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RoboRay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, RoboRay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever say \u0022never\u0022...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair enough I shouldn\u0027t have said \u0022never\u0022.\u00A0 It can be done.\u00A0 But as your screenshot shows it requires large\u00A0wings on the booster,\u00A0wings that might be\u00A0larger than the shuttle\u0027s wings, to achieve something that is aerodynamically stable.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dimas152","CreatedById":179714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-22T05:42:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nactually sxt had a folding wing\u003Cbr\u003E\nidk if it\u0027s re-entry proof\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-22T11:39:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223403352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529646159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022[INDO]dimas_1502\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, [INDO]dimas_1502 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nactually sxt had a folding wing\u003Cbr\u003E\nidk if it\u0027s re-entry proof\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbal Reusability Expansion has a folding wing mount for flyback boosters too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoboRay","CreatedById":46556,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-22T13:38:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223403327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529640799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AVaughan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, AVaughan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair enough I shouldn\u0027t have said \u0022never\u0022.\u00A0 It can be done.\u00A0 But as your screenshot shows it requires large\u00A0wings on the booster,\u00A0wings that might be\u00A0larger than the shuttle\u0027s wings, to achieve something that is aerodynamically stable.\u00A0 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe launch vehicle\u0027s wings have to be larger than the ones on the spaceplane atop the stack, yes.\u00A0 That would have been the case for Dyna-Soar as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Dyna-Soar_on_Titan_booster.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/Dyna-Soar_on_Titan_booster.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-22T13:38:20Z\u0022 title=\u002206/22/2018 01:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by RoboRay\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-23T18:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^ Well, that\u0027s just a goofy looking thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154640-rocket-in-my-pocket/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154640\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154640-rocket-in-my-pocket/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/a\u003E, Did you ever misalign the wing on redocking and not realize it till it was too late?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-23T19:31:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223404148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221529778489\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154640-rocket-in-my-pocket/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154640\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154640-rocket-in-my-pocket/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/a\u003E, Did you ever misalign the wing on redocking and not realize it till it was too late?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually misalignment was the rule not the exception to be honest lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I could get it within 5 degrees I was usually happy with that, it might pull a bit to one side but it was still manageable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt only flew a handful\u00A0of missions, and I think I only got it \u0022perfectly\u0022 aligned once. The more interesting question is \u0022Did I ever accidentally hit it and send it twirling off into space?\u0022 ...Yes, yes I did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-01T15:06:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would love retractable/foldable wings... just as I would love retractable/fold-able rover wheels... like those found in the Kerbal Planetary Base Systems mod (the making history retractable rover wheels don\u0027t have enough range between deployed and retracted for my purposes)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIdeally something like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022584c612df7cde8931f17c06b7fca2941.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022509\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.pinimg.com/originals/58/4c/61/584c612df7cde8931f17c06b7fca2941.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/76KpWsf3Ljw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(the animation is a bit incorrect, the wings would swing out, then rotate, doing it simultaneously results in the clipping that you can see in the video).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried to make designs that fit in a mk3 cargo bay, I havn\u0027t used a dockable wing like the poster above... maybe I should have, these dockable aircraft look bad, and land horribly (I wasn\u0027t able to bring them to a stop successfully on the ground of\u00A0the target body... which is more challenging to land on than kerbin)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese looked and flew horribly, they were abandoned:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uN4FPwd.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/uN4FPwd.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022T0SCBKs.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/T0SCBKs.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022eyoE8wM.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/eyoE8wM.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BTru2XW.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/BTru2XW.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor launching winged craft via rockets however, the solution is rather simple, have them at the bottom of the craft:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00226xcH869.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/6xcH869.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow if you don\u0027t want it directly inline, you can do two on each side for easy balance, or put in the extra tweaks to make asymetric designs (such as STS style designs) work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Yzx9xBb.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Yzx9xBb.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe final transfer stage had to rotate 180 degrees in this design... but that is due to specific peculiarities of my design which also included an orbiting relay and an inflatable heat shield\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022SkclmXm.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/SkclmXm.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}